          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Folio of the Blue Qurʾān, Shelfmark: AKM 248; Qurʾānic Text: 2:148-150; Lines per page: 15; Dimensions: 285 x 353 mm; Script style: kūfī, type D; Estimated date of production: 800-1000. It is not known if the page on display is the recto or the verso page. The website of the Aga Khan Museum has the folloing information: "Qur’an Folio, (Q 2: 148–150), Accession Number: AKM 248; Place:North Africa, Iraq, or Iran; Dimensions:28.5 x 35.3 cm; Date:9th–10th centuries; Materials and Technique:Gold and silver on blue-dyed parchment." For an updated overview of sister fragments, see the detailed catalogue  entry by Marcus Fraser on a sister fragment of the Blue Qurʾān kept by <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/2/vers/286/handschrift/1458">Qatar National Library, call number HC.MS. 03223</ref>. </p>
            </summary>
